<subSubSection id="7ADEBCF9BD4CFFBFFF17FA2E4BB1F8D4" pageId="7" pageNumber="462" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="327BEF72BD4CFFBFFF17FA2E4BB1F8D4" blockId="7.[151,1437,153,1835]" pageId="7" pageNumber="462">
Remarks. This new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="F5C494F1BD4CFFBFFD57FA2D4D3AFA3C" authorityName="Kang, Yao et Yang" authorityYear="2013" box="[647,798,1449,1475]" class="Insecta" family="Ptychopteridae" genus="Ptychoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="462" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lushuiensis">
<emphasis id="00B03360BD4CFFBFFD57FA2D4D3AFA3C" box="[647,798,1449,1475]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="462">P. lushuiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="4AD3AFE2BD4CFFBFFCB2FA2E4D8CFA3C" box="[866,936,1449,1475]" name="China" pageId="7" pageNumber="462">China</collectingCountry>
, but it can be separated from the latter by the second tergum of abdomen mostly brownish, the projection of epandrium curved ventrally, the lobe on middle area of gonostylus tongue-shaped and the posterior margin of hypandrium with a triangular projection medially. In 
<taxonomicName id="F5C494F1BD4CFFBFFA58FA754F37F9D0" authorityName="Kang, Yao et Yang" authorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Ptychopteridae" genus="Ptychoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="462" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lushuiensis">
<emphasis id="00B03360BD4CFFBFFA58FA754F37F9D0" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="462">P. lushuiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the second tergum of abdomen is mostly yellowish, the projection of epandrium suddenly bends into a right angle at middle area, the lobe on middle area of gonostylus is digitiform and the posterior margin of hypandrium has a pair of hook-shaped projections medially. The new species is also similar to 
<taxonomicName id="F5C494F1BD4CFFBFFB99F9D94ACDF988" authorityName="Alexander" authorityYear="1924" box="[1097,1257,1629,1655]" class="Insecta" family="Ptychopteridae" genus="Ptychoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="462" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formosensis">
<emphasis id="00B03360BD4CFFBFFB99F9D94ACDF988" box="[1097,1257,1629,1655]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="462">P. formosensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="4AD3AFE2BD4CFFBFFAFBF9DA4B4AF988" box="[1323,1390,1629,1655]" name="China" pageId="7" pageNumber="462">China</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="4AD3AFE2BD4CFFBFFF47F9064EFEF964" box="[151,218,1665,1691]" name="Japan" pageId="7" pageNumber="462">Japan</collectingCountry>
, but it can be easily separated from the latter by the fifth and sixth terga of abdomen uniformly dark brown, the sixth and seventh sterna of abdomen brown, the dorsal lobe of apical gonostylus hook-shaped and the posterior margin of hypandrium with a pair of L-shaped projections. In 
<taxonomicName id="F5C494F1BD4CFFBFFC86F94D4DDCF91C" authorityName="Alexander" authorityYear="1924" box="[854,1016,1737,1763]" class="Insecta" family="Ptychopteridae" genus="Ptychoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="462" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formosensis">
<emphasis id="00B03360BD4CFFBFFC86F94D4DDCF91C" box="[854,1016,1737,1763]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="462">P. formosensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the fifth and sixth terga of abdomen are yellow with posterior margins black, the sixth and seventh sterna of abdomen are yellow, the dorsal lobe of apical gonostylus is digitiform and the posterior margin of hypandrium has a pair of large rounded flap-shaped lobes.
</paragraph>
